OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|34|  positive results should be confirmed before definitive therapy.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|35|  Additional testing methods may be helpful in detecting abnormalities or||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|36|  in clinical management.||||||F

OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|30|  Comment:  The kidney demonstrates lupus nephritis with a prominent class||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|31|  V lupus with deposits of IGG, IGA, C3, C1Q and kappa,  lambda present||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|32|  the throughout the glomerular basement membranes with prominent||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|33|  subepithelial and intramembranous deposits in glomerular capillary||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|34|  basement membranes.  There are also occasional subendothelial and||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|35|  mesangial deposits with prominent active crescents consistent with a||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|36|  component of class III lupus nephritis.  There is absence of diffuse||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|37|  proliferative change in glomeruli.  The crescents are consistent with||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|38|  focal active lupus nephritis, but a serum ANCA test is recommend to rule||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|39|  out a superimposed vasculitic syndrome. There is only minimal chronic||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|40|  damage seen in the kidney at the present time with a mild increase in||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|41|  interstitial fibrosis without significant increased globally sclerotic||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|42|  glomeruli or tubular atrophy or fibrous crescents seen.||||||F

OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|50|  Clinical Diagnosis/History:  ARF, lupus.  The patient is a 31-year-old||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|51|  who was diagnosed with lupus approximately 2 1/2 years with rash||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|52|  alopecia malaise and treated with Prednisone and also Plaquenil although||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|53|  she has not been on Plaquenil for approximately 9-10 months.  She had a||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|54|  history of lupus coagulant and was treated with Coumadin after a DVT in||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|55|  2010.  She developed gross hematuria earlier in the month and was taken||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|56|  off her Coumadin and was started on high dose Prednisone.  She gained 20||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|57|  lbs.  She has dyspnea and developed leg pain, chest pain, and shortness||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|58|  of breath and was brought in for possible pulmonary emboli.  She has||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|59|  gross hematuria which improved off the Coumadin.  She has joint aches.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|60|  She also has low grade fevers.  Her creatinine has increased to 2.0.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|61|  She also has anemia and pancytopenia.  Her family history is significant||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|62|  for polycystic kidney disease on her mother's side.  She is currently on||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|63|  Coumadin and Prednisone 30 mg a day.  On physical exam, her blood||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|64|  pressure is 141/92.  She has 1+ edema of her extremities with the left||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|65|  greater the right.  She has no rash.  Her hemoglobin is 8.2 with||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|66|  platelets of 153,000, BUN of 34 and creatinine of 2 with an INR of 2.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|67|  Her baseline creatinine is 0.6.  SSA and SSB antibodies are normal.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|68|  SMRNP antibody is normal.  Serum protein electrophoresis reveals an||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|69|  albumin of 2.6 and a total protein of 5.2 grams per deciliter.  Serum||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|70|  immunofixation is negative for a monoclonal protein.  Immature||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|71|  reticulocyte fraction is increased.  On 11/8/11, the patient's||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|72|  creatinine was 1.2 and on 6/10/2010 the creatinine was 0.63 and on||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|73|  11/30/2011 it was 2.02.  Double stranded DNA was elevated at 20.  Serum||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|74|  C3 was decreased at 68.9 milligrams per deciliter and C4 was decreased||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|75|  at 6.3 mg per deciliter.  IGG Coombs test was positive.  C3 Coombs test||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|76|  was also positive.  The patient has a warm immune antibody in the serum.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|77|  Analysis revealed 300 mg/dl of protein and a large amount of blood and||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|78|  many calcium oxalate crystals.  An ANA is positive with greater than 320||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|79|  with a homogenous pattern.  On 2009, the patient had a speckled pattern||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|80|  with a titer of 180.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|81|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|82|  Gross Description:||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|83|  Received in formalin labeled with the patient's name "Jennifer Roth" and||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|84|  designated "left kidney" are four thin, tan, soft tissue core(s), 0.4 up||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|85|  to 1.3 cm in greatest dimension.   All 3/1.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|86|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|87|  Light Microscopy: Sections submitted for light microscopy contain||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|88|  approximately 31 glomeruli with approximately 5 epimembranous crescents.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|89|  Crescents are cellular without prominent fibrosis.  There is focal||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|90|  fibrin associated with the crescents.   In the glomeruli without||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|91|  crescents there is absence of prominent cell proliferation without||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|92|  increased neutrophils.  In the glomeruli with glomerular crescents there||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|93|  are breaks in the glomerular basement membranes seen on the Jones silver||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|94|  stain.  There are no membranoproliferative changes within glomeruli.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|95|  There are prominent epimembranous spikes seen in the Jones silver stain.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|96|  There is a mild increase in interstitial fibrosis (approximately 5%).||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|97|  The tubules have changes consistent with acute tubular damage.  There is||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|98|  no vasculitis involving interlobular arteries present.  There is a mild||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|99|  increase in chronic interstitial inflammation present.  There are red||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|100|  cells present within casts.  There is medial thickening present in||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|101|  interlobular arteries.  There is increased muscle hyperplasia around||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|102|  tubules.  Special stains utilized for assistance in interpretation of||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|103|  the renal biopsy include a PAS stain, a Jone's silver stain, and a||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|104|  trichrome stain.||||||F
